# C4D_MMDTool Project Structure

Cinema 4D plugin for importing and managing MMD (MikuMikuDance) model/animation data. Supports PMX/PMD models and VMD/VPD animation formats.

## Directory Layout

- `source/` — Plugin source code (active development, promoted from former `refactoring/`)
- `old/` — Legacy source code archive (do not modify or build)
- `res/S24_up/` — Plugin resources (descriptions, dialogs, strings, MMD data)
- `dependency/` — Third-party dependency sources (bullet3, libMMD, yaml-cpp)
  - `dependency/bullet3`, `dependency/libMMD` — Third-party sources; built via `add_subdirectory` from `sdk_*` (no `dependency/install` required)
- `cmake/` — Project-level common CMake modules
  - `cmake/mmdtool_plugin_common.cmake` — Common source/resource/dependency logic shared by all SDK plugin CMakeLists
  - `cmake/mmdtool_plugin_dependencies.cmake` — Bullet3 + libMMD subdirectory integration
- `sdk_2026/` — Primary SDK project (CMake build, baseline for presets and tooling)
- `sdk_r20/` … `sdk_2025/` — Other supported SDK projects (all share the same `source/` and `res/`)
  - Each `sdk_*/plugins/mmdtool/project/CMakeLists.txt` — SDK-specific thin wrapper over the common CMake layer

## Source Code Structure (`source/`)

- `main.cpp` — Plugin entry point (PluginStart/Stop/Message)
- `CMTSceneManager.*` — Scene manager (PMX/VMD import core logic)
- `cmt_tools_manager.*` / `cmt_tools_config_manager.*` — Tools/config managers
- `module/core/cmt_marco.h` — Common macros, SDK compat shims, and type aliases
- `module/tools/object/` — C4D object plugins (model/bone/mesh/joint/rigid/morph/camera manager)
- `module/tools/tag/mmd_bone.*` — MMD bone tag
- `module/tools/loader/vmd_loader.*` — VMD animation loader
- `module/tools/material/` — MMD material handling (standard, RedShift, Octane, Corona)
- `module/ui/` — Dialogs (tools, name conversion, VMD camera import)
- `utils/` — Utility functions (all header-only `.hpp`)

## External Dependency Include Patterns

| Dependency | Include Pattern |
|------------|----------------|
| libMMD | `#include "libMMD/Model/MMD/PMXFile.h"` |
| yaml-cpp | `#include "yaml-cpp/yaml.h"` |
| C4D resources | `#include "description/OMMDBoneManager.h"` |
| C4D symbols | `#include <c4d_symbols.h>` |

## Build Process

1. Optional: from repo root, `cmake --preset dev-windows` and `cmake --build --preset cmt-deps-build` to smoke-test `dependency/`; plugin builds compile deps inside each `sdk_*` configure without this step
2. `cd sdk_2026 && cmake --preset windows_vs2022_v143`
3. `cmake --build _build_msvc --config Debug`

Works the same for any supported SDK — replace `sdk_2026` with the target SDK directory (e.g. `sdk_r20`, `sdk_2024`).

CMake: `cmake/mmdtool_plugin_dependencies.cmake` exposes `mmdtool_plugin_dependencies_add(<repo root>)` for Bullet3 + libMMD via `add_subdirectory` into `${CMAKE_BINARY_DIR}/cmt_deps/...` (SDK builds → e.g. `_build_msvc/sdk_2026/cmt_deps`). `cmake/mmdtool_plugin_common.cmake` provides `cmt_setup_mmdtool_plugin()` shared by all SDK plugin CMakeLists. `cmt-clean-deps` removes legacy `dependency/*/build`, `dependency/install`, root `_build_msvc/cmt_deps`, and globbed `_build_*/*/cmt_deps` (per-SDK trees). Configure the repo root CMake project with `-B _build_msvc`, then `cmake --build _build_msvc --target cmt-clean-deps`. For a full wipe including all SDK outputs, use `cmt-clean`.

CMakeLists.txt automatically creates Junctions during configure via `MaxonTargets_CreateDirectoryLink`:
- `sdk_*/plugins/mmdtool/source` → `source/`
- `sdk_*/plugins/mmdtool/res` → `res/S24_up/`

No manual symlinks needed. `projectdefinition.txt` is for reference only and is not parsed.

## Dependencies

| Library | Type | Purpose |
|---------|------|---------|
| libMMD | Static lib | MMD format parsing |
| bullet3 | Static lib | Physics engine (libMMD private dep, plugin does not include directly) |
| yaml-cpp | Static lib | YAML config parsing |
| GLM | Header-only | Math library (libMMD public dep) |

Debug libraries use `_Debug` suffix (e.g. `libMMD_Debug.lib`).
